<div class="prose">

<p>Five real-world scenarios modelled on documented tectonic settings: <strong>Tōhoku</strong> (subduction megathrust), <strong>Anatolian / Istanbul</strong> (transform), <strong>Merapi</strong> (stratovolcano), <strong>Cascadia</strong> (subduction), and <strong>Hawaii</strong> (hotspot shield). Pick a scenario, spend a fixed budget on housing, hospitals, schools, and engineering technologies (base isolation, tsunami walls, early-warning systems, lahar diversion). Run the simulation — a real disaster strikes — and the data tells you which decisions saved lives.</p>

<div class="callout warn">
  <div class="callout-title">v1 reference build — v2 in active development</div>
  <p>The simulator embedded below is the <strong>v1 reference build</strong>. It has three scenarios you can play right now: <strong>Cascadia Coast</strong> (subduction), <strong>San Andreas Crossing</strong> (transform), and a <strong>generic volcano</strong>. The five named, city-anchored scenarios (Tōhoku, Anatolian/Istanbul, Merapi, Cascadia, Hawaii) and the auto-logging Sessions Sheet arrive in <strong>v2</strong>, currently in development.</p>
  <p>Until v2 ships, map your <a href="/units/unit-3/assessment-hazard-profile/">Hazard Profile</a> city to the closest v1 analog:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tokyo / Sendai / Anchorage / Seattle / Portland / Lima</strong> (subduction cities) → play <strong>Cascadia Coast</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Istanbul / Wellington / Kathmandu / Los Angeles</strong> (transform-shaking cities) → play <strong>San Andreas Crossing</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Yogyakarta / Manila</strong> (stratovolcano cities) → play the <strong>generic volcano</strong> scenario</li>
    <li><strong>Hilo</strong> (hotspot shield) → no direct v1 analog; talk to Mr. Ignash about an alternative scenario</li>
  </ul>
  <p>For now, <strong>screenshot your v1 attempts</strong> (final score, grade, budget used) into your engineering journal — same iteration discipline, manual logging.</p>
</div>

<div class="callout">
  <div class="callout-title">Sessions auto-log (v2)</div>
  Once v2 ships: sign in with your school Google account; every attempt saves automatically to the Sessions Sheet — placements, budget used, population saved, score, and grade. You don't need to record anything manually; just play the scenario at least three times for the <a href="/units/unit-3/assessment-engineering-portfolio/">Engineering Portfolio</a>.
</div>

